17.051 | Ethics of Energy Policy (New) | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=17.051 Ethics of Energy Policy (New) | prereq:none instructors:L. Stanczyk term:Acad Year 2016-2017: Not offered Acad Year 2017-2018: U (Fall) description:Explores fundamental ethical problems that arise in the context of energy policy. Topics include the ethics of climate change and emissions reduction policies; international and intergenerational justice as central problems of energy policy; the ethics of natural resource depletion and conservation; the ethics of energy consumption decisions by individuals, households and firms; the proper scope of market forms of regulation in the energy policy arena; and conflicts between utilitarian and rights-based frameworks for evaluating energy policies.  3-0-9 units. HASS-S
